manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Fall in love with our award winning WubbaNub Pacifier, the original part plush, part pacifier. The patented WubbaNub design is sure to be your baby’s first friend. The unique style of the original WubbaNub Pacifier allows it to remain near baby’s mouth, easy to grasp, nearly impossible to lose and may assist baby to self soothe. WubbaNub is distributed in hospitals, NICU and well-baby units nationwide and is made with a 100% silicone pacifier, a non-latex and BPA, PVC and Phthalate-free. The durable one-piece construction of the pacifier means no germs hiding between cracks. WubbaNub is a safety-first company that mandates all infant/baby products are completely safety tested. NOTE: WubbaNub Pacifiers purchased online are packaged in a clear polybag with header card that further describes features and benefits. For additional details and support please refer to the links below.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for newborns
reviews.reviewText: Our 10 week old just starting taking a pacifier. She loves the soothies and the wubanubs allow her more control while being adorable. They are not super easy to clean, but very helpful for really little ones. And who doesn’t love a moose?!?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2018
reviews.reviewText: This is a brilliant product!We introduced our son to pacifiers at 2 months and quickly found he (like alot of babies) would drop and lose his pacifier. We did not like the idea of getting a pacifier leash so we did a bit of looking and found wannanub.When you get one though go ahead and buy two (we bought different animals so he would not get fixated on one.) The reason I suggest buying two is: (1) you always have the possibly of losing one (sorry foxy, we didn't mean to lose you) and (2) you can wash them with your baby's clothes on gentle.After a year the pacifiers became worn, but you can buy the avent pacifiers 2 pack and replace it for a couple bucks. (I'm a decent seamstress, but you don't need to be, just cut the threads where the pacifier is sewn in, pull out the old pacifier, put the new one in, and use a thimble with a thick needle to get nice tight stiches. If you don't have the strenght you can use a husband with pliers.)The best part about this product is I found our son is weaning himself off of it much quicker than some of my friend's children and ALL BY HIMSELF! He is 16 months and rarely used the pacifier part of the wannanub. I recently removed the pacifier on both of his wannanubs and sewed them up and they just turned into nap stuffies. He did ge a bit upset, but there was no huge fuss like I've seen in the past and he did suck on the feet the first two nights, but stopped that on his own and now just snuggles with them.I was never a fan of pacifiers because I hated how fixated some toddlers become. Wannanub has made a great product that allows newborns the ability to grab their own pacifiers and cuddle buddies, babies the ability to easily carry and put down their pacifiers for an easier ability to crawl and learn, and a great method for toddlers to transition away from their pacifiers.I plan to add this product to all my baby shower gifts!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these Pacifiers
reviews.reviewText: WubbaNub Animal Pacifiers are so adorable. and my grandson loves them. What I like the best, is they are easy to locate throughout the house. An 18 month old like to toss his things ( or whatever object he gets his hands on )in some of the strangest places. WubbaNub Animal are easy to spot under, behind, and in-between furniture. The nipple can withstand a lot of chewing from those new baby incisors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It’s a favorite!
reviews.reviewText: Our 3 month old LOVES this pacifier. It’s so easy for him to get back in his mouth after it falls out or he pulls it out. It’s also like he likes the light weight feeling on his chest from the moose. Our 5 year old has named it “Mr. Moose” and has a song for his baby brother. We love this pacifier and have another as well, buts it’s a different animal.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and soft
reviews.reviewText: This is the cutest little thing and it's helping my son use his fine motor skills because he is working on grabbing and holding it. The stuffed animal doesn't come off the pacifier making it a little difficult to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good, cute pacifier
reviews.reviewText: Our baby loves his moose wubbanub! It helps him learn to coordinate his arms by having him try to move his arms to get the pacifier back in his mouth. We have to spot clean the animal part, which makes it a little more difficult to clean. Plus it’s so cute!
